<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-12-26T11:40:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-12-26T11:40:00-05:00" n="81" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d81">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">839.6463/79: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in the Dominican Republic</hi>
                                (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Russell</hi></persName>)
                                <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Santo
                                        Domingo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-12-26T12:00:00-04:40"><hi rend="italic">December 26,
                                        1922—noon</hi></date>.<lb/>[Received December 27—5
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>49. Minister of the Interior informs me that the municipality Santiago
                            has given option of 120 days concession of Santo Domingo Light and Power
                            Company to Santo Domingo Brewing Company represented by Kalb, Austrian,
                            and Contreras, Mexican.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Russell</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>